    <h2 class="text-primary-dark">Introduction</h2>
    <p>Welcome to NebulaTextbook. This Acceptable Use Policy (AUP) governs the use of our platform and services. By using NebulaTextbook, you agree to comply with the terms outlined in this policy. The goal of this policy is to maintain a secure, positive, and respectful environment for all users, particularly university students accessing educational materials.</p>

    <h2 class="text-primary-dark">Acceptable Use</h2>
    <p>You may use NebulaTextbook for legitimate educational purposes in accordance with the following guidelines:</p>
    <ul class="list-group">
        <li class="list-group-item">Access educational resources and materials for personal academic use.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">Engage with course content, including interactive features, quizzes, and exercises.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">Communicate respectfully with instructors, fellow students, and administrators within the platform.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-primary-dark">Prohibited Activities</h2>
    <p>Users of NebulaTextbook are prohibited from engaging in any of the following activities:</p>
    <ul class="list-group">
        <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Illegal Activities:</strong> Any action that violates federal, state, or local laws, including intellectual property laws and FERPA regulations.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Disruptive Behavior:</strong> Engaging in activities that disrupt the functionality of the platform, such as attempting to hack or gain unauthorized access to any part of the site.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Harassment:</strong> Any form of harassment, discrimination, or offensive behavior toward other users, including but not limited to verbal abuse, cyberbullying, or inappropriate comments.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Inappropriate Content:</strong> Uploading, sharing, or distributing any content that is obscene, defamatory, or offensive in nature.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Spamming:</strong> Sending unsolicited emails or messages to other users, or engaging in marketing or advertising without permission.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Violation of Privacy:</strong> Collecting, sharing, or misusing personal information of other users in violation of FERPA laws and university privacy regulations.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-primary-dark">Account Security</h2>
    <p>Users are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of their account credentials. You must not share your login information or allow others to access your account. Any unauthorized use of your account should be reported immediately to NebulaTextbook administrators.</p>

    <h2 class="text-primary-dark">Monitoring and Enforcement</h2>
    <p>NebulaTextbook reserves the right to monitor user activities and content to ensure compliance with this policy. In cases of suspected violations, NebulaTextbook may take appropriate action, including warning the user, restricting access, or permanently terminating the user’s account.</p>

    <h2 class="text-primary-dark">Consequences of Policy Violations</h2>
    <p>Failure to adhere to this Acceptable Use Policy may result in consequences ranging from temporary suspension of account access to permanent termination of your account. In serious cases, legal action may be taken if applicable laws have been violated.</p>

    <h2 class="text-primary-dark">Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>NebulaTextbook may update this Acceptable Use Policy from time to time. We encourage users to review the policy regularly to stay informed of any changes. All updates will be reflected on this page with the corresponding date of the last update.</p>

